{"parse":{"title":"hospital","pageid":8408,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|Hospital|hôpital}}\n==English==\n{{wp}}\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alter|en|hospitale||obsolete}}\n\n===Etymology===\n[[File:Hospital room ubt.jpeg|thumb|A room in a hospital]]\n{{etymon|en|:inh|enm:hospital|tree=1}}\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|hospital}}, {{m|enm|hospitall}}, from {{der|en|fro|hospital}} (Modern {{cog|fr|hôpital}}), from {{der|en|la-lat|hospitālis|hospitālis, hospitāle|hospice, shelter, guesthouse}}, from noun use of {{der|en|la|hospitālis||hospitable}}, from {{m|la|hospes||host, guest}}. {{doublet|en|hotel|hostel}}. Displaced native {{ncog|enm|lechehous}}, from {{ncog|ang|lǣċehūs|lit=doctor house}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈhɒs.pɪ.tl̩/|a=RP}}\n** {{audio|en|En-uk-hospital.ogg|a=UK}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈɒs.pɪ.tl̩/|a=obsolete,RP}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈhɑs.pɪ.tl̩/|/ˈhɑs.pɪ.ɾl̩/|a=GenAm}}\n** {{audio|en|en-us-hospital.ogg|a=US}}\n* {{hyph|en|hos|pit|al}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun|~}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|Q16917}}A large [[medical]] [[facility]], usually in a building with multiple floors, where seriously ill or injured [[patient]]s are given extensive medical or [[surgical]] treatment.\n#: {{ux|en|Luckily an ambulance arrived quickly and he was rushed to '''hospital'''.|q=UK}}\n#: {{ux|en|Luckily an ambulance arrived quickly and he was rushed to the '''hospital'''.|q=US}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|author=w:Sameer P. Sarkar|chapter=Mental health law and the mentally disordered offender|editors=Annie Bartlett; Gill McGauley|title=Forensic Mental Health: Concepts, Systems, and Practice|publisher=w:Oxford University Press|year=2010|section=section 3 (Law)|page=265|isbn=978-0-19-856685-4|passage=This section of the Act gives the court powers to assess whether treatment is going to be beneficial and hence whether '''hospital''' is a suitable disposal option.}}\n# A [[building]] founded for the [[long-term]] [[care]] of its [[resident]]s, such as an [[almshouse]].\n#: {{ux|en|The foundling '''hospital''' took in abandoned children and educated them.}}\n# {{lb|en|obsolete}} A place of [[lodging]].\n#* {{RQ:Spenser Faerie Queene|book=II|canto=IX|passage={{...}} they spide a goodly castle, plast / Foreby a riuer in a pleasaunt dale, / Which choosing for that euenings '''hospitale''', / They thither marcht {{...}}}}\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{l|en|sickhouse}}\n\n====Hyponyms====\n* {{l|en|clinic}} {{q|small hospitals}}; {{l|en|field hospital}} {{q|mobile, military}}; {{l|en|asylum}}, {{l|en|institution}} {{q|mental health}}; {{l|en|leprosarium}}, {{l|en|leprosery}}, {{l|en|lazar house}} {{q|leprosy}}; {{l|en|lazaret}}, {{l|en|lazaretto}} {{q|port quarantine}}\n\n====Coordinate terms====\n* {{l|en|infirmary}}, {{l|en|nurse}}{{l|en|-'s|'s}} {{l|en|office}} {{q|rooms within a larger institution such as a school}}; {{l|en|surgery}} {{q|UK}}, {{l|en|doctor's office}} {{q|separate medical practices}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en|hospicentric|Hospital Row|hospitalman|superhospital|base hospital\n|antihospital\n|cottage hospital\n|field hospital\n|hospital corner\n|hospital fever\n|hospital gown|hospital bag\n|hospital pass\n|hospital soap\n|hospital ship|psych hospital\n|hospitalise\n|hospitalism|hospital bed|hospital sock|put someone in hospital\n|hospitalist\n|hospitalization\n|hospitalize\n|in hospital\n|in the hospital\n|in-hospital\n|interhospital\n|intrahospital\n|lock hospital\n|mental hospital\n|military hospital\n|multihospital\n|nonhospital\n|posthospital\n|prehospital\n|teaching hospital\n|veterinary hospital\n|children's hospital|general hospital|hospital corpsman|hospital gangrene|hospital order|maternity hospital|psychiatric hospital|hospital pharmacy}}\n\n====Related terms====\n{{col|en\n|hospice\n|hospitable\n|hospitality\n|hospitaller\n|host\n}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|am|ሆስፒታል|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|bal|اسپتال|tr=ispatāl|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|bn|হসপিটাল<tr:hospiṭal>|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ceb|hospital|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|gu|હોસ્પિટલ|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|mr|इस्पितळ|हॉस्पिटल|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|mh|aujpitōļ|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ms|hospital|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|sd|اسپتال|tr=ispatāl|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|st|sepetlele|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|sw|hospitali|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ta|ஆஸ்பத்திரி|alts=1|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|tg|ҳоспитал|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|zu|isibhedlela|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|shi|ṣṣbiṭar|bor=1}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|large medical facility}}{{multitrans|data=\n* Abkhaz: {{tt|ab|ахәшәтәырҭа}}\n* Afrikaans: {{tt+|af|hospitaal}}\n* Albanian: {{tt+|sq|spital|m}}\n* Altai:\n*: Southern Altai: {{t|alt|эмчилик}}\n* Amharic: {{tt|am|ሐኪም ቤት}}, {{tt|am|ሆስፒታል}}\n* Arabic: {{tt+|ar|مُسْتَشْفًى|m}}, {{tt|ar|مَارِسْتَان|m}}\n*: Chadian Arabic: {{t|shu|لبتان|tr=labtān|m}}\n*: Egyptian Arabic: {{tt|arz|مستشفة|f|tr=mustašfa}}, {{tt|arz|قشلة|}} {{q|obsolete}}\n*: Hijazi Arabic: {{tt|acw|مُسْتَشْفى|tr=mustašfa}}\n*: Moroccan Arabic: {{tt|ary|سبيطار|m|tr=sbīṭār}}\n*: North Levantine Arabic: {{tt|apc|خستخانة}} {{q|Syria}}\n*: South Levantine Arabic: {{tt|ajp|مُسْتَشْفًى|tr=mustašfa}}, {{tt|ajp|إسبيطَار}} {{q|Galilee}}, {{tt|ajp|سْبِيتَار}} {{q|Palestine}}\n* Aragonese: {{tt|an|espital|m}}\n* Aramaic:\n*: Assyrian Neo-Aramaic: {{tt|aii|ܒܹܝܬ ܟܪ̈ܝܼܗܹܐ|tr=bēt krīhe|m}}\n* Armenian: {{tt+|hy|հիվանդանոց}}\n* Assamese: {{tt|as|হস্পিতাল}}\n* Asturian: {{tt|ast|hospital|m}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{tt+|az|xəstəxana}}, {{tt+|az|hospital}}\n* Baluchi: {{tt|bal|اسپتال|tr=ispatāl}}\n* Bashkir: {{tt|ba|дауахана}}, {{tt|ba|хәстәхана}}\n* Basque: {{tt|eu|ospitale}}, {{tt|eu|erietxe}}\n* Belarusian: {{tt|be|бальні́ца|f}}, {{tt|be|бо́льніца|f}}, {{tt|be|шпіта́ль|m}}, {{tt|be|ляка́рня|f}}\n* Bengali: {{tt+|bn|হাসপাতাল}}\n* Bole: {{tt|bol|azibiti}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt+|bg|бо́лница|f}}\n* Burmese: {{tt+|my|ဆေးရုံ}}\n* Buryat: {{tt|bua|эмнэлгэ}}\n* Carpathian Rusyn: {{tt|rue|бо́лниця|f}}, {{tt|rue|шпіта́ль|m}}, {{tt|rue|шпіта́льня|f}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|hospital|m}}\n* Chechen: {{tt|ce|больница}}\n* Cherokee: {{tt|chr|ᏧᏂᏢᎩᎢ}}\n* Cheyenne: {{tt|chy|naa'émâhéó'o}}\n* Chichewa: {{t