{tt|ms|rumah sakit}}\n* Malayalam: {{tt+|ml|ആശുപത്രി}}\n* Maltese: {{tt|mt|sptar|m}}\n* Manx: {{tt|gv|spittal|m}}, {{tt|gv|thie lheihys|m}}\n* Marathi: {{tt+|mr|रुग्णालय|n}}, {{tt|mr|इस्पितळ|n}}, {{tt|mr|हॉस्पिटल|n}}, {{tt|mr|दवाखाना|m}}\n* Mari:\n*: Eastern Mari: {{tt|mhr|больнице}}, {{tt|mhr|госпиталь}}, {{tt|mhr|лечебнице}}, {{tt|mhr|стационар}}, {{tt|mhr|эмер}}, {{tt|mhr|эмлымвер}}\n* Marshallese: {{t|mh|aujpitōļ}}\n* Mongolian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt+|mn|эмнэлэг}}, {{tt|mn|эмнэлэг хороо}} {{qual|China}}, {{tt|mn|госпиталь}}, {{tt+|mn|больниц}}\n*: Mongolian script: {{tt|mn|ᠡᠮᠨᠡᠯᠭᠡ}}, {{tt|mn|ᠡᠮᠨᠡᠯᠭᠡ ᠬᠣᠷᠢᠶ᠎ᠠ}}, {{tt|mn|ᠾᠣᠰᠫᠢᠲ᠋ᠠᠯᠢ}}, {{tt|mn|ᠪᠣᠯᠢᠨᠢᠼᠠ}}\n* Naga:\n*: Khiamniungan Naga: {{t|kix|mūolījàm}}\n* Navajo: {{tt|nv|azeeʼálʼį́}}\n* Ndebele:\n*: Northern Ndebele: {{tt|nd|isibhedlela}}\n* Nepali: {{tt+|ne|चिकित्सालय}}, {{tt+|ne|अस्पताल}}\n* Newar: {{tt|new|चिकित्सालय}}\n* Ngamo: {{tt|nbh|janar}}\n* Niuean: {{t|niu|fale gagao}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{tt+|nb|sykehus|n}}, {{tt+|nb|sjukehus|n}}\n*: Nynorsk: {{tt|nn|sjukehus|n}}\n* Occitan: {{tt+|oc|espital|m}}, {{tt+|oc|espitau|m}}\n* Odia: {{tt|or|ଡାକ୍ତରଖାନା}}\n* Old English: {{tt|ang|lǣċehūs|n}}\n* Ossetian: {{tt|os|рынчындон}}\n* Pannonian Rusyn: {{tt|rsk|шпиталь|m-in}}, {{tt|rsk|больнїца|f}}\n* Papiamentu: {{tt|pap|hòspital}}\n* Pashto: {{tt+|ps|روغتون|m|tr=roǧtun}}, {{tt+|ps|شفاخانه|f|tr=šafāxāna}}, {{tt|ps|هاسپيټل|m|tr=hāspiṭal}}, {{tt|ps|هسپټال|m|tr=haspaṭāl}}\n* Persian:\n*: Dari: {{tt|prs|شَفَاخَانَه}}\n*: Iranian Persian: {{tt|fa-ira|بیمارِسْتان}}, {{tt|fa-ira|بیمارْخانِه}}, {{tt|fa-ira|شَفاخانِه}}, {{tt|fa-ira|مَریضْخانِه}}\n* Pitjantjatjara: {{tt|pjt|atjupitila}}\n* Plautdietsch: {{tt|pdt|Hospitol|n}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|szpital|m}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|hospital|m}}\n* Punjabi:\n*: Gurmukhi: {{tt+|pa|ਹਸਪਤਾਲ|m}}\n* Quechua: {{tt|qu|unquna wasi}}, {{tt|qu|jampina wasi}}\n* Romanian: {{tt+|ro|spital|n}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|больни́ца|f}}, {{tt+|ru|го́спиталь|m}} {{qualifier|usually a military hospital}}, {{tt+|ru|кли́ника|f}}, {{tt+|ru|лече́бница|f}}\n* Sami:\n*: Northern Sami: {{tt|se|buohcceviessu}}, {{tt|se|buhcciidviessu}}\n* Samoan: {{tt|sm|falema'i}}\n* Sanskrit: {{tt|sa|चिकित्सालय|m}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{tt|gd|taigh-leighis|m}}, {{tt|gd|taigh-eiridinn|m}}, {{tt|gd|taigh-tinnis|m}}, {{tt|gd|ospadal|m}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt+|sh|бо́лница|f}}\n*: Latin: {{tt+|sh|bólnica|f}}\n* Shona: {{tt|sn|chipatara}}\n* Sicilian: {{tt+|scn|spitali|m}}\n* Sindhi: {{tt+|sd|اسپتال|f|tr=ispatāl}}\n* Sinhalese: {{tt+|si|ආරෝග්‍යශාලා}}, {{tt|si|රෝහල්}}\n* Slovak: {{tt+|sk|nemocnica|f}}\n* Slovene: {{tt|sl|bolnišnica|f}}, {{tt+|sl|bolnica|f}}\n* Somali: {{tt|so|isbitaal}}\n* Sorbian:\n*: Lower Sorbian: {{tt|dsb|chórownja|f}}\n*: Upper Sorbian: {{tt|hsb|chorownja|f}}\n* Sotho: {{t|st|sepetlele}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|hospital|m}}, {{t+|es|nosocomio|m}} {{qualifier|medical term}}\n* Swahili: {{tt+|sw|hospitali|cIX}}\n* Swazi: {{tt|ss|esibhedlela}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|sjukhus|n}}, {{tt+|sv|lasarett|n}}\n* Tagalog: {{tt+|tl|ospital}}, {{tt|tl|pagamutan}}\n* Tahitian: {{t|ty|fare maʻi}}\n* Tajik: {{tt+|tg|бемористон}}, {{tt+|tg|касалхона}}, {{tt+|tg|беморхона}}, {{t|tg|маризхона}}, {{t|tg|шифохона}}\n* Tamil: {{tt+|ta|மருத்துவமனை}}, {{tt+|ta|ஆஸ்பத்திரி}}\n* Tatar: {{tt|tt|хастаханә}}, {{tt+|tt|шифаханә}}\n* Telugu: {{tt+|te|ఆసుపత్రి}}, {{tt+|te|వైద్యశాల}}, {{tt+|te|దవాఖానా}} {{qualifier|Telangana}}, {{tt|te|చికిత్సాశాల}}, {{tt|te|చికిత్సాలయము}}\n* Tetum: {{tt|tet|ospitál}}, {{tt|tet|uma-moras}}\n* Thai: {{tt+|th|โรงพยาบาล}}\n* Tibetan: {{tt|bo|སྨན་ཁང}}\n* Tigrinya: {{tt|ti|ሆስፒታል}}, {{tt|ti|ቤት ሕክምና}}\n* Tok Pisin: {{tt|tpi|haus sik}}\n* Tokelauan: {{t|tkl|falemai}}\n* Tongan: {{t|to|fale mahaki}}\n* Tumbuka: {{t|tum|chipatala}}\n* Turkish: {{tt+|tr|hastane}}, {{tt|tr|emlerge}}, {{tt+|tr|sayrılarevi}}\n*: Ottoman Turkish: {{t|ota|خسته‌خانه|tr=hastahane}}\n* Turkmen: {{tt|tk|keselhana}}, {{tt|tk|gospital}}\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt|tk|кеселхана}}, {{tt|tk|госпитал}}\n* Ukrainian: {{tt+|uk|ліка́рня|f}}, {{tt|uk|шпита́ль|m}}, {{tt|uk|го́спіталь|m}}, {{tt|uk|болни́ця|f}}\n* Urdu: {{tt|ur|ہَسْپَتال|m}}, {{t|ur|شِفا خانَہ|m}}, {{t|ur|اَسْپَتال|m}}, {{t|ur|دارُ الشِّفا|m|tr=dāru ś-śifā}}, {{t|ur|بِیمارِسْتان}}, {{tt|ur|مُسْتَشْفیٰ}}, {{tt|ur|بِیمار خانَہ|m}}, {{tt|ur|مَرِیض خانَہ|m}}, {{tt|ur|صِحَت خانَہ|m}}\n* Uyghur: {{tt|ug|دوختورخانا}}, {{tt|ug|دوختۇرخانا}}, {{t|ug|شىپاخانا}}, {{t|ug|بالنىتسا}}\n* Uzbek: {{tt+|uz|kasalxona}}, {{tt+|uz|shifoxona}}\n* Venetan: {{tt|vec|ospedal|m}}, {{tt|vec|ospeal|m}}\n* Vietnamese: {{tt+|vi|bệnh viện}} ({{tt|vi|病院}}), {{tt+|vi|nhà thương}}, {{tt+|vi|y viện}} ({{tt|vi|醫院}})\n* Volapük: {{t+|vo|malädanöp}}\n* Warray: {{tt|wrz|baláy-tambalan}}\n* Welsh: {{tt+|cy|ysbyty|m}}\n* Xhosa: {{tt|xh|esibhedlele}}\n* Yiddish: {{tt|yi|שפּיטאָל|m}}\n* Yoruba: {{tt|yo|ilé-ìwòsàn}}\n* Zhuang: {{tt|za|yihyen}}\n* Zulu: {{tt|zu|isibhedlela}}\n}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Adjective===\n{{en-adj}}\n\n# {{lb|en|obsolete}} [[hospitable|Hospitable]].\n#* {{RQ:Fielding Tom Jones\n|passage=At last the Ocean, that '''hospital''' friend to the wretched, opened her capacious arms to receive him; and he instantly resolved to accept her kind invitation.}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|relational to hospitals}}\n* Marshallese: {{t|mh|aujpitōļ}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|hospitalario}}, {{t|es|nosocomial}} {{qualifier|medical term}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{C|en|Organizations|Buildings|Healthcare}}\n\n==Asturian==\n\n===Etymology===\nRecent borrowing from {{bor|ast|es|hospital}} from {{bor|ast|la-lat|hospitālis|hospitālis, hospitāle|hospice, shelter, guesthouse}}, from {{der|ast|la|hospitālis||hospitable}}. Compare native {{l|ast|hespital}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{ast-pr}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{ast-noun|m|hospitales}}\n\n# {{l|en|hospital}} {{gl|building}}\n\n==Catalan==\n{{wp|ca:}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|ca|la-lat|hospitālis|hospitālis, hospitāle|hospice, shelter, guesthouse}}, noun use of {{der|ca|la|hospitālis||hospitable}}. Doublet of the inherited {{dbt|ca|hostal|notext=1}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{ca-IPA}}\n* {{audio|ca|LL-Q7026 (cat)-Unjoanqualsevol-hospital.wav|a=Catalonia}}\n* {{rhyme|ca|al|s=3}}\n* {{hyph|ca|hos|pi|tal}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{ca-noun|m}}\n\n# {{l|en|hospital}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|ca|hospital psiquiàtric}}\n* {{l|ca|hospitalitzar}}\n\n====Related terms====\n* {{l|ca|hospitalitat}}\n* {{l|ca|hospici}}\n* {{l|ca|hostal}}\n* {{l|ca|hoste}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:ca:IEC2}}\n* {{R:ca:GDLC}}\n* {{R:ca:DNV}}\n* {{R:ca:DCVB}}\n\n{{C|ca|Buildings}}\n\n==Cebuano==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|ceb|en|hospital}}, borrowed from {{der|ceb|fro|hospital}}, from {{der|ceb|la|hospitālis||hospitable}}, from {{m|la|hospes||host, guest}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{ceb-IPA|hóspitál}}\n* {{audio|ceb|LL-Q33239 (ceb)-Howdy.carabao-hospital.wav|Audio}}\n* {{rhyme|ceb|al|s=3}}\n* {{hyph|ceb|hos|pi|tal}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{ceb-noun|hóspitál|b=+}}\n\n# a {{l|en|hospital}}\n#: {{syn|ceb|ospital|tambalanan}}\n\n{{C|ceb|Buildings}}\n\n==Danish==\n\n===Etymology===\nBorrowed from {{bor|da|la-lat|hospitāle|hospitālis, hospitāle|hospital, guesthouse}}, from the neuter form of {{der|da|la|hospitālis||hospitable}}, from {{m|la|hospes||host, guest, stranger}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|da|/hɔspitaːl/|[hɔsb̥iˈtˢæːˀl]}} or {{IPA|da|/hospitaːl/|[hosb̥iˈtˢæːˀl]}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{da-noun|et|er}}\n\n# {{l|en|hospital}}\n\n====Inflection====\n{{da-noun-infl|et|er}}\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{l|da|sygehus|g=n}}\n\n====Further reading====\n* {{pedia|lang=da}}\n\n{{C|da|Buildings|Medicine}}\n\n==French==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{fr-muteh}} {{fr-IPA|hôpital}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-WikiLucas00-hospital.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Lyon>>)}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{fr-noun|m}}\n\n# {{obsolete spelling of|fr|hôpital}}\n\n==Galician==\n{{wp|gl:}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|gl|:inh|roa-opt:espital<id:hospital>|id=medical facility|tree=1}}\nFrom {{inh|gl|roa-opt|hospital}}, {{m|roa-opt|espital}}, {{m|roa-opt|spital}}, borrowed from {{bor|gl|la-lat|hospitālis|hospitālis, hospitāle|hospice, shelter, guesthouse}}, from {{der|gl|la|hospitālis||hospitable}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{gl-pr|họspital}}\n* {{hyph|gl|hos|pi|tal}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{gl-noun|m}}\n\n# {{l|en|hospital}}\n#: {{ux|gl|Foi visitar un enfermo ao '''hospital'''. Un '''hospital''' privado.|He went to visit a sick person in the '''hospital'''. A private '''hospital'''.}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|gl|hospitalizar}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:gl:DRAG}}\n\n==Interlingua==\n{{was fwotd|ia|2020|April|28}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|ia|/hos.piˈtal/}}\n\n===Adjective===\n{{ia-adj}}\n\n# [[hospitable]]\n#* {{quote-journal\n|ia\n|work=Panorama in Interlingua\n|year=1992\n|title=Un septimana in asuncion\n|author=Ramiro Castro\n|issue=martio-april\n|volume=1992\n|passage=Le populo es multo '''hospital''' e amabile.\n|translation=The people are very '''hospitable''' and amiable.}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{ia-noun|es}}\n\n# {{l|en|hospital}}\n#* {{quote-journal|ia|year=1959|month=March|author=A. Donald Merritt; Bernard F. Fetter|title=Toxic Hepatic Necrosis (Hepatitis) due to Isoniazid: Report of a Case with Cirrhosis and Death due to Hemorrhage from Esophageal Varices|journal=Annals of Internal Medicine|page=810\n|passage=Esseva constatate plus tarde que illa habeva recipite streptomycina, isoniazido, e acido para-aminosalicylic un anno previemente a un altere '''hospital'''.|t=It was established later that she had received streptomycin, isoniazid and para-aminosalicylic acid a year earlier at another '''hospital'''.}}\n\n==Malay==\n\n===Etymology===\nBorrowed from {{bor|ms|en|hospital}} or {{bor|ms|nl|hospitaal}},<ref>{{cite-book|last=Kwik Khing Djoen |year=1923|title=Kitab Vortaro: Segala Perkatahan-Perkatahan Asing Jang Soeda Oemoem Di Goena Ken Di Dalem Soerat-Soerat Kabar Melayoe|location=Batavia|publisher= Sin Po|page=144}}</ref> both ultimately from {{der|ms|fro|hospital}}, from {{der|ms|la|hospitālis}}. Displaced {{m|ms|rumah sakit}} within Malaysia by the 1960s during the [[:w:Konfrontasi|Konfrontasi]].<ref>{{cite-book|title=Gaya bahasa sastera Melayu|author1=Umar Junus|publisher=Dewan Bahasa dan Pustaka Malaysia|year=2010|page=95}}</ref>\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{ms-IPA}}\n* {{hyph|ms|hos|pi|tal}}\n* {{rhymes|ms|ital}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{ms-noun|j=هوسڤيتل}}\n\n# {{l|en|hospital}}\n#: {{syn|ms|rumah sakit<qq:Malay populated areas of Indonesia>}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|iba|sepital|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|zmi|sopita|bor=1}}\n\n===References===\n<references/>\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:PRPM}}\n\n==Middle English==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alter|enm|hospitale|hospitall|hospitalle|hospitel|hospytal|hospytale|hospytall|ospitale}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|enm|:bor|fro:hospital}}\n{{bor+|enm|fro|hospital}}, from {{der|enm|la|hospitālis}}, {{m|la|hospitāle}}. {{doublet|enm|hostel}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|enm|/ɔspiˈtal/|/ˈɔspital/}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{enm-noun|hospitals}}\n\n# A [[hostel]] or [[guesthouse]]; a place of accommodation or lodging.\n# A [[shelter]] for the poor, ill or otherwise needy.\n# A place of refuge; a retreat or redoubt.\n# The [[w:Knights Hospitaller|Knights Hospitaller]] {{gloss|a religious order}}\n\n====Related terms====\n* {{l|enm|hospitalarye}}\n* {{l|enm|hospitalite}}\n* {{l|enm|hospiteler}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|en|hospital}} {{see desc}}\n* {{desc|sco|hospital}}\n\n====References====\n* {{R:MED Online|entry=hospitāl |pos=n |id=MED21265 |accessdate=2018-08-07}}\n\n===Adjective===\n{{enm-adj}}\n\n# [[hospitable]]\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|en|hospital|qq=obsolete}}\n\n====References====\n* {{R:MED Online|entry=hospitāl |pos=adj |id=MED21266 |accessdate=2018-08-07}}\n\n{{C|enm|Buildings and structures|Christianity|Hotels|Housing}}\n\n==Middle French==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|frm|fro|hospital}} (Modern {{cog|fr|hôpital}}), borrowed from {{bor|frm|la-lat|hospitālis|hospitālis, hospitāle|hospice, shelter, guesthouse}} from {{der|frm|la|hospitālis||hospitable}}, from {{m|la|hospes||host, guest}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{frm-noun|m|hospitaulx}}\n\n# {{l|en|hospital}} {{gloss|medical}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|fr|hôpital}}\n\n==Old French==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|fro|:bor|la-lat:hospitālis}}\nBorrowed from {{bor|fro|la-lat|hospitālis|hospitālis, hospitāle|hospice, shelter, guesthouse}}, from {{der|fro|la|hospitālis||hospitable}}, from {{m|la|hospes||host, guest}}. Compare the inherited {{m|fro|ostel}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{fro-noun|m}}\n\n# {{l|en|hospital}} {{gloss|medical}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|xno|ospitel}}\n** {{desc|mga|ospitél|bor=1}}\n*** {{desc|ga|ospidéal}}\n*** {{desc|gd|ospadal}}\n* {{desctree|frm|hospital}}\n* {{desctree|nl|hospitaal|bor=1}}\n* {{desctree|enm|hospital|bor=1|noalts=1}}\n* {{desc|ru|госпиталь|bor=1}}\n\n===Adjective===\n{{fro-adj}}\n\n# [[hospitable]]; [[welcoming]]\n\n====Declension====\n{{fro-decl-adj|ssm=[[hospitals]], [[hospitaus]]|opm=[[hospitals]], [[hospitaus]]}}\n\n==Old Occitan==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alter|pro|ospital|espital}}\n\n===Etymology===\nBorrowed from {{bor|pro|la|hospitāle||hospital; guesthouse}}, noun use of the neuter form of {{m|la|hospitālis||pertaining to a host or guest}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|pro|/us.piˈtal/}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{pro-noun|m}}\n\n# {{l|en|hospital}}\n#* {{quote-book|pro|year=12<sup>th</sup> c.|title=Lo codi|trans-title=The Code|original=Codex Justinianeus|by=w:Justinian I|passage=A gleisas et a '''hospitals'''|translation=to churches and '''hospitals'''}}\n# One of several [[religious]] [[order]]s.\n\n====Related terms====\n* {{l|pro|hospitaleir}}\n* {{l|pro|hospitalitat}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|oc|espital}}\n\n==Portuguese==\n{{wp|pt:}}\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|pt|espital||obsolete}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|pt|:inh|roa-opt:espital<id:hospital>|id=medical facility|tree=1}}\nFrom {{inh|pt|roa-opt|hospital}}, {{m|roa-opt|espital}}, {{m|roa-opt|spital}}, borrowed from {{der|pt|la-lat|hospitālis||hospice, shelter, guesthouse}}, from {{der|pt|la|hospitālis||hospitable}}. Doublet of the inherited {{doublet|pt|hospedal|notext=1}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{pt-IPA}}\n* {{IPA|pt|/ɔs.piˈtaw/|a=Northeast Brazil}}\n* {{audio|pt|LL-Q5146 (por)-Santamarcanda-hospital.wav|a=<<Portugal>> (<<Porto>>)}}\n* {{rhymes|pt|al|q1=Portugal|aw|q2=Brazil|s=3}}\n* {{hyphenation|pt|hos|pi|tal}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{pt-noun|m}}\n\n# {{l|en|hospital}}\n#: {{syn|pt|nosocómio}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|pt|hospitalar}}\n* {{l|pt|hospitalizar}}\n\n====Related terms====\n{{col|pt|hospedaria|hospitalário|hóspede|hospedeiro|hospedar|hospício|hospitaleiro|hospitalidade|inóspito|inospitalidade}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|kea|ospital}}\n* {{desc|bn|হাসপাতাল|der=1}}\n* {{desc|gu|ઇસ્પિતાલ|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|inc-hnd|bor=1}} {{see desc}}\n** {{desc|hi|अस्पताल}}\n** {{desc|ur|اسپتال|tr=aspatāl}}\n* {{desc|hrx|Hospital|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|kn|ಆಸ್ಪತ್ರೆ|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|kok|ओश्पिताल|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|mr|इस्पितळ|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|tet|ospitál|bor=1}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:pt:Priberam}}\n\n{{C|pt|Buildings}}\n\n==Spanish==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|es|:bor|la-lat:hospitāle<id:guestroom>|id=medical facility|tree=1}}\n{{bor+|es|la-lat|hospitāle||hospice, shelter, guesthouse}}, from {{der|es|la|hospitālis||hospitable}}. {{doublet|es|hostal}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{es-pr|+<audio:Es-hospital.wav<a:Spain>>}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{es-noun|m}}\n\n# {{l|en|hospital}}\n#: {{syn|es|nosocomio}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|es|hospital psiquiátrico}}\n\n====Related terms====\n{{col|es|hospitalidad|hospicio|hostal|hospedar|huésped}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|ceb|ospital|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|bcl|ospital|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|kyj|ospital|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|tl|ospital|bor=1}}\n\n====See also====\n{{col|es|clínica}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:es:DRAE}}\n\n{{C|es|Buildings}}\n\n==Swedish==\n{{wp|sv:}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|sv|la-med|hospitale}}, nominalisation of {{der|sv|la|hospitalis||hospitality}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{sv-noun|n}} {{lb|sv|archaic}}\n\n# {{lb|sv|11th century}} [[lodging]] for travelers\n# {{lb|sv|middle age}} [[leprosarium]]; care facility for the [[leprous]]\n#* {{quote-book|sv|year=1844|author=w:Magnus Jacob Crusenstolpe|title=Morianen, eller Holstein-Gottorpiska huset i Sverige. Tidsbilder, började på fästningen. Sjette och sista delen|page=44|url=https://litteraturbanken.se/f%C3%B6rfattare/CrusenstolpeMJ/titlar/MorianenSjette/sida/44/faksimil|text=Hennes person kan liknas vid ett '''hospital''', som utanpå är likt ett nymåladt palats, men hyser inom sig död, sjukdom och förskräckelse; {{...}}|t=Her person may be likened to a '''leprosarium''', which on the outside is like a newly painted palace, but harbors within it death, disease, and horror; {{...}}}}\n# {{lb|sv|15th century}} care facility for the [[elderly]], [[disabled]], and [[sick]]\n#: {{syn|sv|helgeandshus}}\n# {{lb|sv|19th century}} [[mental hospital]]\n#* {{quote-book|sv|year=1835|author={{w|Victor August Altén|lang=sv}}|title=Dikter II|chapter=Jorden|trans-chapter=Earth|page=94|pageurl=https://litteraturbanken.se/f%C3%B6rfattare/Alt%C3%A9nVA/titlar/Dikter2/sida/108/faksimil|text=Mången tror den är ett '''hospital''',<br>då han ser så många dårar samla<br> sig uti dess stora gästningssal,<br> och, som blinda, kring dess väggar famla.|t=Many believe it's a '''madhouse''',<br>when they see so many fools gather,<br>in its large reception hall,<br>and, like the blind, stumble around its walls.}}\n#* {{quote-book|sv|year=1843–1846|author=w:August Blanche|title=Theater-stycken I|chapter=En trappa upp och på nedra botten, eller Grosshandlaren och Klädmäklaren [1843]|page=76|url=https://litteraturbanken.se/f%C3%B6rfattare/BlancheA/titlar/Theaterstycken1/sida/80/faksimil|text=Hvar har ni fått de der idéerna ifrån? ni måtte ha rymt från något '''hospital''' i Frankrike?|t=Where did you get those ideas from?  you must have escaped from some '''mental institution''' in France?}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{sv-infl-noun-n-zero}}\n\n====See also====\n{{col|sv|sjukhus<t:hospital><lit:sick-house>|lasarett<t:hospital>}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:svenska.se|so}}\n* {{R:svenska.se|saol}}\n* {{R:svenska.se|saob}}"}}